==English==
=== Etymology ===
from Middle French "''blonde''" (feminine). The masculine form of the word is "''blond''." 

In the English language, it is only one a few distinct words where the gender differentiation is actually reflected in the spelling of the word (i.e. ''She is a blonde woman.'' vs. ''He is a blond man.''), even though it is a relatively common occurence in other languages. 

